text: Vinca may refer to: * Vinca, one of two genera of plants with the common name Periwinkle * Catharanthus roseus, an annual bedding plant common name Vinca * Vinca, the Hungarian name for Vinţa village, Lupșa Commune, Alba County, Romania * Vinça, a commune of the Pyrénées-Orientales département in France * Vinca (software), a program to reverse VNC for remote support * Vinca massacre, a massacre of 162 Italian civilians carried out by the 16th SS Panzergrenadier Division Reichsführer-SS ==See also== * Vinča (disambiguation)
title: Vinca (disambiguation)
